		<p><addressee>Reverend Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
		<p>I have taken up my Pen to inform you&#44;<lb/> what the remnant of <placeName>Israel</placeName> are doing<lb/> for South&#44; namely in the State of <placeName>Texas</placeName><lb/> There are not many in the State&#44; but still<lb/> you will find a sprinkling of them in every<lb/> village&#44; some are adhering to our faith&#44; others<lb/> again are intermarrying with &#40;<add>Hebrew</add>&#41;</p>
		<p>I must not <sic>ommit</sic> to mention&#44; what happened<lb/> in our city&#44; a <persName>Mr E. Cohen</persName> lately from <placeName>England</placeName><lb/> whose wife was <sic>delievered</sic> of a Boy&#44; with an<lb/> indomatible courage&#44; he concluded at once<lb/> to perform <sic>circumciesion</sic> himself&#44; as we have<lb/> no &#40;<add>Hebrew</add>&#41; nearer than <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>&#44; he was<lb/> persuaded by some of our coreligionist&#44; to wait<lb/> till the child could be taken to <placeName>New Orleans</placeName><lb/> or to send for a &#40;<add>Hebrew</add>&#41; his reply was as our<lb/> father <persName>Abraham</persName> has performed it on the <date>8th Day</date><lb/> why should he not do it&#44; the child is<lb/> doing well&#44; the ceremony was performed in<lb/> the presence of a Surgeon</p>
		<p rend="align(right)">S</p>
		<p>Truly yours</p>
		<p><persName role="author">M Suligson</persName></p>
		<p><placeName>Galveston</placeName> <date>November 1851</date></p>
		<p><persName>Mr Leeser</persName> any Errors above&#44; please correct it</p> 
		<p>my respects to <persName>Mr Hackenberg</persName></p>
          
